content:
Which of the following structures is a
 
tissue
 
 
Options
 
 
A) Vessel
 
element
 
 
B)
 
Blood
 
 
C) Sieve tube
 
element
 
 
D)
 
Erythrocyte
 
 
The correct answer is
 
B.
 
 
Explanation
:
 
 
In biology, tissue is a cellular organizational level intermediate between cells and
 
a complete organ. A tissue is an ensemble of similar cells from the same origin
 
that together carry out a specific function. Organs are then formed by the
 
functional grouping together of multiple tissues.
